com.nokia.maps.map

Interface MapObject

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    MapCircle, MapContainer, MapMarker, MapPolygon, MapPolyline, MapRectangle, MapStandardMarker

    public interface MapObject
    This interface defines is the basis for all visual objects shown in a map, including the map itself. Instances of this class are responsible for identifying UI state changes and automatically trigger a redraw. It depends on the platform how and when this redraw is performed.

    The z-index of a MapObject instance is relative to the container. The z-index is used to specify the stacking order in a MapContainer. Objects with the highest values are placed on top. The overall stack order in a map is defined hierarchically:

    1. Level in the MapContainer hierarchy.
    2. Order in the container's list of MapObjects.

    Markers have special handling for z- ordering. For more information, see MapMarker and MapStandardMarker.

    See Also:
    MapMarker, MapContainer, MapStandardMarker,

        This method retrieves a boolean value indicating whether the MapObject is visible.
